{"questionId":"13445163","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>One of the eigenvectors of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">T</mi></math> is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find another, non-parallel, eigenvector and interpret it in context.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>+</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>M1</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">v</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo mathvariant=\"bold\">&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;(accept any multiples of this answer)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>&nbsp; A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">v</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;means that in the long term the ratio of veg to non-veg is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>2</mn></math><br>(in the long term one-third of students will be veg and two-thirds will not)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[3 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13445163","referenceCode":"23N.1.AHL.TZ0.15c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find another, non-parallel, eigenvector and interpret it in con